page.title: 14Keadby Wharf
page.content: Ships registered in Germany,Belgium, Holland,Sweden,Denmark,Russia and Spain come to the wharf,which is privately owned,bringing materials from a variety of places.65% of its business is dealing with imports and 35% with exports.Imports include sand, timber,grain,anthracite,steel,pig iron and magnacite.Exports include grain and finished steel.Imports are taken by road to all parts of the country. Being a small private wharf handling costs are cheaper.Ships come up river on the tide and drop anchor and allow the tide to turn the ship into the wharf.Three men work at this wharf which is a subsidiary for the larger one across the river.Ships are unloaded by bobcat into cranes which can lift up to 50 tonnes.The men work a 6 hour shift.There are 2 lay by berths either side of the wharf.
